    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-02-06T10:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-02-06T10:50:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <head>122. Summary of Decisions of a Meeting of the Senior Washington Special
                    Actions Group<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d122fn1">Source: National
                        Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–79,
                            <gloss target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> (Principals Only) Vietnam 2–6–71.
                        No classification marking. According to the separate minutes of the meeting,
                        it ended at 2:15 p.m. (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-02-06T10:50:00-05:00">February 6, 1971, 10:50 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Southeast Asia Dry Season Campaign</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry Kissinger</persName>, Chairman</item>
                    <item>State—<persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>; <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWH1">William H. Sullivan</persName>; Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_BE1">Bunker</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Defense—<persName corresp="#p_PD1">David Packard</persName>; <persName
                            corresp="#p_DDJ1">Dennis Doolin</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Richard
                            Helms</persName>; Mr. <persName>Donahue</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>—Admiral <persName corresp="#p_MTH1"
                            >Thomas Moorer</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>—Col. <persName corresp="#p_KRT1">Richard
                            Kennedy</persName>; <persName corresp="#p_HJH1">John
                            Holdridge</persName>; <persName corresp="#p_SWR1">W. R.
                            Smyser</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>WH Staff—<persName corresp="#p_HHR1">H.R. Haldeman</persName>; <persName
                            corresp="#p_ZRL1">Ronald Ziegler</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">SUMMARY OF DECISIONS</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The press statements on Operation <gloss target="#t_LAMSON7191"
                            >Lamson</gloss> should include the separate release of the <gloss
                            target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> statement and the <persName
                            corresp="#p_ZRL1">Ziegler</persName> statement<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d122fn2">
                            <persName corresp="#p_ZRL1">Ziegler</persName> included in a memorandum
                            to <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>, February 5, the
                            drafts of a statement to be released by <gloss target="#t_MACV1"
                                >MACV</gloss> after <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName>
                            released his statement and a statement to be released by <persName
                                corresp="#p_HDZ1">Henkin</persName> confirming the <gloss
                                target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> and <persName corresp="#p_NVT1"
                                >Thieu</persName> statements. (Ibid., Box H–79, <gloss
                                target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> (Principals Only) Vietnam 2–6–71) On
                            February 9, Zeigler gave a news briefing on Laos. See <hi rend="italic"
                                >Public Papers: <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>,
                                1971</hi>, p. 1221.</note> to <pb facs="0406" n="367"
                            xml:id="pg_367"/> which a reference to artillery firing from <gloss
                            target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss> should be added. The statement should read
                        that U.S. artillery support from positions in South Vietnam will be
                        available to the <gloss target="#t_ARVN1">ARVN</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The President wanted Pompidou informed in advance consistent with
                        security.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
